@ThinkingandTinkering 
Thank you for putting out great content. What I enjoy most, is that you prove a historical point of view also.
I watch you're channel because you either help me see something I've missed or you help me come up with a different design that does the task better.

@ThinkingandTinkering I want to thank you for this clip. You treated it with your wonderful smile and humour, but the topic isn't so light. It was often discussed when we were building a new storage/transport system, especially when we were discussing safety of the machines. Where to draw that line? That elusive line where "it's good enough" becomes "that's madness". You can have a safety feature. But then you wonder what will happen if that feature fails? So, let's make safety feature for that safety feature... And you suddenly fall into a rabbit hole that never ends.
Knowing when to stop and say "that's good enough" at the right point, is a very difficult and precious skill.
Good judgement comes with experience and a lot of that comes from bad judgement 😉
